caption: Exceptional! Delicious food, friendly  and attentive service, warm ambiance, reasonable prices. A totally joyous experience!
Pleasant staff, awesome food and ownership!

This is a very happy establishment. The food is fresh and flavorful , and the (German and Austrian) beer selection is outstanding. There is live music Thursday through Sunday: Thursday and Friday featuring Anthony on guitar, playing classics from the 60's and 70's; Saturday and Sunday, Maxx performs European classics on the accordian. You are always well fed and entertained at Himmel's!
Great and yummy food, I loved the character this place has, and the staff members were super nice. I will surely visit here when I’m around.
Delicious potatoes and schnitzel. The mushroom schnitzel was sooo good. The potatoes were flavorful, but a little dry.
We ordered Himmel’s for our Christmas dinner. I was blown away, the chicken schnitzel was amazing. I will come back here again and again.

When you are there you feel like family, the food is always solid and and the atmosphere is pure Germany. They are very safe with there pandemic protocol and have a totally outside dining area for beers and sausages as well as a great to-go menu.
I visit this spot a lot since I work nearby. I must say the customer service is always good and they keep the spot clean at all times. Pricing is convenient and they serve big portions.

The spicy sausage here is delicious and the huge beers are even better! Himmel's is a great place to eat, watch a game and hang out with friends. They have a pretty good selection of beers here. I had the hef and the Oktoberfest. Definitely wasn't disappointed. I'll probably come back to watch the World Series and indulge in some of their other options.
Probably the best German food in the city. Not your typical German restaurant, but rather modern and welcoming.
We love the authentic food, back patio, and wonderful music when the band plays
The place offers a vast variety of fresh food. I like dining here. Staff members are always super nice, pricing is reasonable and the place is always neat.
This restaurant is extraordinary and broad, the food was delightful and the rates were very inexpensive. quickly, efficient service and very friendly staff. Will definitely recommend this restaurant.
Tried this place in the past with my friend and I am obsessed ever since. I love the awesome mood and delightful dishes and drinks. They never disappoint.
Last of the decent German restaurants in Lincoln Square!
Amazing Chicken Parmesan
This spot is great and broad, the food was delightful and the prices were very fair. quickly, productive service and very amiable staff members. I highly recommend this place.
Best in the hood since Brauhaus!
Home cooking flavors, portions that will last a few days, and surprisingly good neopolitan style pizza. As a New Yorker its a nice change to what these Chicagoians call pizza.
The place is great and roomy, the menu was delightful and the rates were very inexpensive. fast, productive service and very affable staff members. I recommend this place.
This spot is excellent! Reasonable rates, considerable dishes and the staff are consistently kind.

Carried out food for an early Saturday dinner - it was superb! Highly recommend the pretzel bread loaf, and the German Table Wine. The red cabbage is to die for, and all the entrees we had were excellent.
Great food and service!

I celebrated my birthday this evening in this great place. I am glad to say that it was a enjoyable evening and the place was unquestionably one of the reasons for the strong evening. The stuff  helped in a gorgeous way, the food was very good and my buddies were extremely  pleased. We shall no dout come back again for more celebrations. thanks very much.

Got take out because of the new norm and it was easy and ready when they said it would be. As for the food, it didn't disappoint in taste or portion size. Glad to have them in the neighborhood and I look forward to ordering there again.
I eat here a lot since I work in the area. I like how the service is always awesome and they keep the spot neat at all times. Pricing is fair and they serve large portions.

I told my friends about this restaurant with my highest recommendations. I go their often. I get very good feedback from my friends. The meals are flavorable and the stuff is efficient and cooperative. Every time  we go to this place we enjoy a delightful evening.  warmly recommended.
Very good wood burning oven pizza,  good beer and bloody mary. Best of all was the service from our bartender/waitress Dajana.
Great time in good ol Lincoln Square!
Great food, Drink and Friendly Staff. Save room for dessert.

Burgers here are made to order and come in a variety of types. Generally they are cooked "medium well", but I have found that ordering them "medium" produces juicy burgers that hold their shape and flavour.
They offer a fantastic range of delicious food. I love eating here. Staff members are always super nice, prices are convenient and the place is always well organised.
We sat outdoors. The atmosphere was quiet and the service was good. Coke unlimited refills add an interesting touch.
Good burger not that expensive. The potatoes are not good and you don't have a lot of choices, I will search for something better...

This is one of my favorite restaurants. The food is delicious, the ambience comfortable and nice, the service attentive. Tonight I listened to a lovely-voiced man and his accompaniment sing and play and got stuffed to the gills with schnitzel. A great restaurant for sure.
Delish classic European snacks!
Exceptional food, very welcoming employees, consistently great vibes. They charge reasonable pricing and the food quality is excellent. Great work.
Finest food, kind employees, consistently great character. They charge convenient pricing and the food quality is good. 5 stars.
I adore this restaurant very much. It has a great ambiance. The kitcen is great. the service is effective and the stuff is courteous. The pay is satisfactory. I definitely recommend.

The food was just okay food and service was quite slow. We were ignored by the staff multiple times and their attitude was that serving us was a bother to them. When the electronic bill arrived at the table on her iPad it had a 20% tip preselected. If I had my way I would have selected 0%. I did give the 15% tip but that's the last time they will see any money from me. For the $40 we spent on our dinner tonight, I felt completely ripped off.
Excellent food and good service A very pleasant experience
Fantastic food, friendly staff, consistently  awesome character. They charge reasonable prices and the food quality is excellent. Keep up the good work.
The food and service were beyond my expectations. I really liked the environment of this place. Excellent spot to take the family out for dinner.

I eat in this lovely spot quite a bit! This is my favorite place to have a bite.  I go there routinely. The food is very good, the workers are courteous and the cost is fair. I like going in this place over a good dinner.
Himmel's Has great, authentic German food and beer. Great local atmosphere and, generally, live music. The wait-staff was extremely nice and generous.

I love this spot! They prepare decent meals, their menu is varied, The chef in that spot is a professional, I love a lot trying all their food. The dishes are always of high class, the attitude towards the visitors  is helpful. I  go often to this restaurant and I was never unsatisfied.  I highly recommend it.
I always come by grabbing some food in this place. I enjoyed the quick customer service and well prepared dishes. Never disappointing.

It's so refreshing to see the owners actively engaged in their business, and creating an authentic experience! The food is both familiar and delicious, only sad I was there for an event and didn't get to try their wood oven pizza yet.
The food is always well prepared and delicious, workers hands out fantastic service. I loved how neat it is and mood. I highly recommend this place.

last night was our first time we visited this magnificent restaurant. But It is absolutely not the last. We had great time with the courteous service, with the exceptional  food and fine drinks and with the decent payment. We will no doubt go back there again.
The beer and schnitzel was amazing! Top notch food and service
Delicious german food

I brought my parents here to enjoy an early holiday meal--it was their first visit--and Himmel's delivered. The pub is decorated for Christmas and has an extra lovely, cozy feel. The food is always delicious and there are options for even the fussiest or most eclectic palette. We enjoyed appetizers, entrees and drinks...my only regret is there was no room for dessert. Live music, singing and dancing on a Sunday afternoon rounded the whole experience out; we left feeling happy and stuffed.
A must stop for German eaters!

This site is my favorite site.  Of all restaurants I know I like it most. I never miss an opportunity to go to that place. Whenever  I want to go to a superb lunch, this is the place that comes straightaway to my head. excellent and many types of  food and a rich menu.great staff members, and agreeable spirit. Not less important, the price is affordable. I sent my friends to this restaurant with great pleasure.
Simply the best German dining with comfortable old time flare
Service was good for a big party, food was okay. The chicken schnitzel was good.
I constantly arrive getting some food in this place. I loved the quick customer service and well prepared food. They never disappoint.
Best place ever! Great food, wonderful people. Awesome ! 5 stars plus!

(Translated by Google) For all German tourists - but not only - "heaven" is an excellent address. You are very hungry. Here two ideals meet: very good food and really filling portions.  (Original) Für alle deutschen Touristen  - aber nicht nur - ist "Himmels" eine ausgezeichnete Adresse. Man nehme ganz viel Hunger mit. Hier treffen zwei Ideale aufeinander: sehr gutes Essen und wirklich sättigende Portionen.
The food was very good.  Attentive service, etc.
Very elegant and convenient spot. They provide generous portions and for economical prices. I loved the meals a lot and the staff members were very friendly and chatty. I recommend this place.
Great real german food and music recomend highly
Darn good German spot!
Food was good with true authentic German flavors.
Great food at fair price. Loved coming here. Live music.
Great food, fair prices
Great steak tartare.   Hard to find.   Delightful staff.   Will definitely come back.
German with a pizza oven

Wonderful place to satisfy your German & Italian cuisine carvings. While it may seem like an unusual combination, they do each one proud. The Italian menu is somewhat limited, however it only offers the best of fair. They hit the mark with every dish. On the German side it's all great, but the Champignon Rahm Schnitzel is the best around. Sehr gut!

Went for my birthday dinner and was soarly disappointed. The place had a nice decor but a weird smell. Maybe wood from a brick oven but definitely not the smell of food. The special at this German restaurant was Taco Tuesday & margaritas. This should've been my first clue to leave. Ww ordered drinks which neither of us liked and sent back. The menu had no rhyme or reason. The appetizers were scattered throughout the menu. The menu can't determine if this is a German, Italian or wanna be mexican restaurant. We ordered the wiener schnitzel. Which was ok. The spaetzle was crunchy which I've never had like that before. The sauerkraut and or red cabbage are served on the plate not in a bowl to contain the juices so if u dont like ur food touching don't order it. Mom ordered the chicken marsala which was so dry it had the texture of liver. All in all it was a major disappointment. I'm a lobg time client of the Chicago Brauhaus and before that the Heidelberg Fass, two truly excellent authentic Geeman restaurants. I have traveled all over Germany and Austria and know a good German meal when I see and taste it This fell extremely short sorry to say.
The pork tenderloin German dish with the spätzle is fantastic. If you have never tried spätzle, definitely this is the place and this is the dish.

What a great place!!! Awesome food especially there bread baked fresh by one of the owners/chef Carol Himmel!!!!  Great service lively and entertaining.  There chicken was fabulously tasty. Easy parking. Cute area of the city. The other owner Diana Himmel Krueger (sisters) is wonderful to her staff and takes extra care and interest in her customers. Fun family run authentic German restaurant. You'll even see Mr& Mrs Himmel Giving it a feel of tradition and  ethnicity! Check out there Sunday brunch I'm definitely going to!!

One of few places where you can get excellent Italian and German food.  Also great German beer and authentic neapolitan pizza. I could do without the live music. I go to dinner for conversation, and concerts for music.
Great food and their white chocolate truffle cheesecske was fantastic!!
Not only is the food quite good, but also a wonderful atmosphere, live music, just great fun!
Wow what a great tasting menu
The Food and Service  is very good. And the Owners are very Extremely  helpful  toward their Geust.Very recocomendable..
Thin crust perfection. They have an imported oven from Italy. Ingredients are fresh. It tastes amazing!

Probably one of the best German places I've ever been.  Each entree can easily feed 2 people and they are amazing.  The spaetzle is home made and incredible. So is the sauerkraut and red cabbage! Even the table bread is amazing - the crust was smokey and like a crunchy pretzel. We topped it all off with the pistachio gelato, which was delicious. They chill the side salads here, which really made them delicious. There was a baby shower happening here while we were here so it looks like they do well with large groups and events too.  Can't recommend enough!

I absolutely love this place! My son brought me here a few years ago and I'm now hooked! Great selection of food and beers. The service is fantastic, it really does feel like like your dining in someone's home. The food is very fresh and delicious! So many layers of flavor...cherry sauce on apple and bacon stuffed chicken breast? Omg! Everything on their menu is awesome!
The waitress was rude, got the order wrong. The table was dirty with bread plates with food stuck on them.  I would mor recommend this place.

Spatzle!!!! Spatzle with the tender pork loins and creamy mushroom sauce! Omggg so delicious paired with a mixed beer. I got a mixed beer of some sort with lemon soda added to it? Sweet and delicious. this place is also crazy packed all the time so prepare to wait!

I like this place for the live music, but the food left me wanting more. Got the wurst plate. And even though it was advertised as having three sausages, it only came with two and a small slice of a third one. A little bit disappointing. Still, a good place for a local live music, even if they are cover bands.
Good German food and beer.
We love Himmels as well as Carol. We were just there for her Superbowl party and buffet- yum. A restaurant that's treats you like family!

The food was unbelievably good. I had the schnitzel and was amazed. Portions for price are veryyy fair. Service quality is good, very friendly people. Lighting was spot on and music was at the right volume to enjoy while still having a conversation. This is the best german resteraunt I've been to in Chicago.
(Translated by Google) Live music, very good attention.  (Original) Música en vivo, atención muy buena.
Had the 3 various sausages.  Good  just not the Brauhaus, good service.
Food was OK service was good
Delicious old school German food.  And the wood pizza oven still turns out tasty options for those days when you're not into Spatzle. Although I can't imagine that happening.

Just okay food. Service was slow. I asked the waitress for the wifi password and her face got distorted as she snarled out she did not know the password. Her attitude was that serving us was a bother to her. When the electronic bill arrived at the table on her iPad it had a 20% tip preselected. If I had my way I would have selected 0%. I did give the 20% tip but that's the last time she will see any money from me. For the $110 we spent on our dinner that Friday night I felt completely ripped off. There are much better choices in restaurants around the city that actually want your business.
We had  a great experience tonight.  True German experience - good food, good music and dancing, great vibe.  Regret not going here before.
Cute, traditional German. Used to be an Italian pizza place. The wood pizza oven is still functioning so you can also get pizza here.
The food is really really good, love the atmosphere and the staff are one of a kind. Love it everytime!!!

Seems to have two types of clientele. 20-something's trying to get drunk at the bar and 40+'s coming for the authentic food. Majority of the staff seems younger then either crowd and out of their element. Nonetheless, service is decently good. Beer and pretzel bread are great.
Love the authentic food and polka
Awesome food, atmosphere
Food is always great. Carol & Diane are magnificent hosts. Can't wait to go back.
Unbelievable food and great music!!!
Outstanding European food.
Huge portions of very good German food.
Great food, delicious chicken sniztel, and love the live entertainment that is not to loud. Owners treat you family.
Wait for an hour and a half for food. After that period a soup was brought. Will not go back.

Eclectic menu of delicious German and some Italian with a brick oven baking up homemade bread and really great pizza. Homemade spatzle offered in several dishes (including soup when we visited). Drink prices are reasonable and wine selection is good.
The food is amazing.  It brought me back to have dinner at my Oma’s house.  We received excellent service at the bar.  Will be back for a 3rd time soon.
great food everytime we go. super friendly staff and owner came to all tables and chatted. will be back with friends
Very charming, friendly. Other than an easily overlooked misstep, we were pleased and will definitely be back!
All around great German cuisine ! German American family owned. The sisters are awesome & sometimes pickled ! LOL !!
Friendly staff and a great selection of German foods. Authentic tastes. I'm hooked.
Excellent food,great staff.

We were surprised by the tremendous quality of the food. It's a quirky small cozy place with an odd mix of decorating. We were there on a Saturday night and there was an accordian player playing everything from traditional German and Italian songs to American classics. The food was outstanding. My only complaints are that the fried calamari legs were chewy and the beer selection was terrible. For a German restaurant to not have an array of German beer is baffling! How can they not have hefeweizen?! Witbier? With an upgrade in beer I'd give it 5 stars.
Great food and atmosphere
Great place! Authentic food and music.
The best pizza in Lincoln Square.
Nice spot for some German food and beer. House specialties are really tasty
Excellent food and friendly service great atmosphere.

Ordered the suaerbraten. Very salty. The spatzle and cabbage were okay. Our waitress was not very friendly and bit slow. The atmosphere was okay, but not German. If you're looking for actual german food I'd recommend looking for another place to go.
Excellent food!
Got the pork shank. Lovely presentation. Fresh and tasty. Particularly liked the pickled cabbage salad and spaetzle. Helpful, friendly service.
Best place to eat in Chicago!
Service was great . My gf liked her dish. I had the duck and it it was chewy and not good. My sides were cold. I'd give it another chance.
Always excellent food and superior service
Midday chill spot
I love this place, one of my favorite restaurants. They serve unbelievable food and service is wonderful.
Below average food and the slowest and worst service in recent memory.
One of our favorites.
They messed up our drinks, pizza and soup. If you want pizza go to Forono Roso. Very disappointing.
Very good German food. Will be back in the near future.
Food was very good. Bread was even better.
Ull never find anywhere what they have 2 offer.
Fair food lousy service. Best spend your hard earned money elsewhere.

Fair at best, when it comes to their Italian fare. They do better with their German choices. The steak is done well, along with their desserts. Unfortunately the room is loud which makes it hard to have a conversation. The service is friendly, and the wine list is ok.
Had probably the best wiener schnitzel I've ever had here. Will return.

If you’re near Himmel’s stop in for some food.  Everything is excellently prepared.  Italian favorites and some of the best German food in the city.  Fabulous home-made breads and portions that will feed a small army - including the kids meals.  Plus the Chef will step out of the kitchen at times to greet the guests and provide some evening music.
Good food, good booze ... if you're looking for good German food in Chicago, Himmel's is the place to go.
Interesting mix of German and Italian food and atmosphere. The schnitzel is pretty good and so are the spaetzles and red cabbage. Haven't had the Italian food here, but it smells great.
Nice place,friendly staff,cold beer.
I love their pizza. Great food and great service .
Great German food. Great atmosphere. Poor server.

This is the first place I found back home that I could get tuna fish and mushroom brick oven pizza. The portions are excellent on all dishes and a variety of foods on the menu, also some popular German dishes. The rib eye is my favorite steak, but I have to have my pizza. Have to call ahead to get order tuna fish, as its not popular on pizza, but worth it to me. Owners are wonderful, chef is superb, my favorite restaurant since around 2002. Great place for a date night, also live music on Thursday night. I know you'll enjoy it.

Hands down the best bucatini and ribeye steak around.  Did I mention the potato salad? Always get a container to go.  The live music on the weekends is the perfect touch to a place where everyone knows your name.  Get ready for an amazing meal. One of our favorites places to eat in Chicago.
Great food, drinks and music

I rarely take time to review resturants, but felt compelled to write here. Slow service, overpriced, food was mediocre to bad, pizza came out at room temperature, music was way to loud. Don't understand why it was German and Italian food, please just pick one.  Great bongos though drum
Live music Thursday& Friday night.

This is a gem of a restaurant! The food is delicious. Something on the menu for everyone. We love the schnitzel and all the fresh salads. We have never had a bad meal and service is great. This is our new favorite Lincoln square spot.
Food is good service is slow

Strong German and Italian influences guide a solid menu of rich flavors cooked up in a cozy and warm restaurant. Loved the Thuringer sausage, spatzle and wood fired pizza. Great bar, great staff, great menu.
Fabulous pizza cook in a real brick oven. Best Italian pizza in Chicago
The German comfort food is beyond delicious though you may never move again

Best German in Lincoln Square..no scratch that, best in the city.  And if you are still craving a wood fired pizza, no worries, they are still available.  The owners will make you feel like you are at home when you come here.  There are no strangers at Himmel's.
Great pizza
Classic German fare in Old German Town

Called to order a delivery the person who answered the phone asked me to hold. She put the phone down and I heard a 5 minute conversation. I hung up and called back. I got someone else, ( I'm sure the other phone was still on the bar) I got my pizza ordered and was told an hour. After 2 hours I finally called to find out why I was still waiting and was told that nobody called the driver to deliver. I was apologized to and told that the pizza would be here in ten minutes. I then asked if the pizza had been sitting there for an hour and a half. They were happy to take my credit card. It would be nice to get dinner...still waiting...
We sat outside and the street is kinda loud.
By far the best German Restaurant in Chicago.  Celebrated mother's 90th b-day there.  Service and food outstanding.  I can't say enough good about this place!!
I loved it. Definitely we will come back. Great service, great atmosphere, great people, delicious food. Made my day.
The bone in rib eye .. The best ..
Love this place!  Outstanding food and great service!
(Translated by Google) Hofbräu on tap and delicious Wiener schnitzel.  (Original) Hofbräu vom Fass und leckeres Wiener Schnitzel.
Good service, decent pizza.

Customer service is horrible. It took nearly an hour to get our entrée. We had to request for bread and it took them a long while to bring it out. The bread was stale... at least a day or 2 old. All in all, we are very disappointed with this visit. The wait staff needs to be better trained. There are many better restaurants in Chicago. We would not recommend this restaurant if you're looking for good service. The food is just fair...nothing to rave about!

First time I drove past this restaurant from appearance and expectation I thought it would present a cozy environment serving authentic German fare.  However, based upon my first (and last) visit I can only recommend this establishment for its cozy environment and nothing more.  It's a restaurant in search of a cuisine that's on the pricey side too!  Which are you Himmel, German or Italian?  The Owner's need to decide what they're trying to present.  I didn't have any Italian food but the German offerings were slim and lacked some major traditional items.  The Sauerbraten was mediocre at best.  Pass this one up. There are plenty of other good German restaurants in Chicago with authentic fare including the big dining room downtown!

The Rahmschnitzel was the best meal I've ever had. Not exaggerating.  The restaurant looks brand new. They also serve pizza because it used to be an Italian restaurant with a wood burning stove.  Went there on a Friday night and it wasn't crowded at all.
Best German food I've had in town.  Great atmosphere and staff.  Go on the weekend and try the Bavarian Pork Shank, it is amazing!
Cozy atmosphere and great pizza

This Lincoln Square neighborhood spot serves Italian and German food. It used to be called Pizza Doc and despite the name change, pizza here is outstanding. Try thin crust white pizza with petite potatoes and fresh rosemary, or grilled vegetable pizza. The use that wood-burning oven well :) Other Italian fare is also available, like pastas. Grilled vegetable antipasto is phenomenal - with very delicate balsamic vinegar reduction. I have not sampled their German dishes. The inside of restaurant and the decor is OK. It does get very noisy on Saturdays (very busy). You see lots of locals and families with kids here. Overall, I like the place because the food I've tasted here is good.
THE FOOD ITS GREAT! REAL ITALIAN FOOD!..
We had such a good time here last night. Food was great, german specials amazing!!! My family had pizza and pasta, excellent. Nice wine list, service was awesome
Pizza D.O.C is amazing.  Great Pizza, amazing speciality dishes - but really its the people.  You walk in the door and you feel a warm welcome...it doesn't get better then that!
My favorite non- Chicago style pizza place in Chicago.

The service was miserable. We had to remind the hostess that we were waiting for a table because she had forgotten and rarely saw our waitress.  The food came out at very different times and the pizza I got was not as it was described on the menu.  It was decent food, but I won't be going back.
not your classic italian-style brick oven pizza but they have some tasty alternatives. service can sometimes be slow
noisy bright, like la cosa vera.   count on antipasta, go for thin   toasted pizza. mangia!
